  "text": "Based on the latest body of evidence, it is hypothesized that mental practice applied in a training regime involving arm function tasks will lead to a significant and long-lasting improvement in stroke patients' arm function. Furthermore, since rehabilitation depends upon the learning of new behaviors (this is associated with brain plasticity), the treatment should include much repetition [CITATION_1] , start early after the stroke [CITATION_2] , be personally rewarding to the patients and provide as much experience as possible of various activities.",
